UID:1534354-1773943200-1773954000@hugohouse.org
SUMMARY:Silent Reading Night
DESCRIPTION:Silent Reading Night – March Edition \nDate: Thursday\, March 19th \nTime: 6:00 PM – 9:00 PM \nTheme: Pages Shared: A Community Book Exchange \nWe wanted to celebrate this month’s silent reading night with a community book exchange themed reading night! Feathered Pages will be tabling for this event. \nEvent Activities: \nCommunity Book Swap \nTo participate in the book swap\, let the front desk know upon arrival and receive your raffle ticket. One book = 1 ticket. Feel free to bring as many books as you would like to swap! \n\nGrab some wrapping paper from the front desk with a blank note card that answers one of these two prompts:\n“Why I loved this book…” or “describe this book in a sentence..”\nWrap up the book and tape the note card to the cover with the answered prompt.\nDrop books at categorized area on the stage\n\n\nFiction\nNonfiction\nRomance\nFantasy/Sci-Fi\nMemoir\n\nRaffle Announcement (at 8:30 PM) \nThere will be up to 5 winners! The prize is a Hugo House tote with books inside! \n \nEvent Itinerary \n6:00 PM – Mix & Mingle \n\nGrab a cup of tea and settle in.\nMeet fellow readers and share what book you’re currently enjoying.\nBYOM – Bring Your Own Mug! Hot water will be available.\n\n6:30 PM – Silent Reading Begins \n\nSettle into your cozy reading spot and dive into your book.\nEnjoy the quiet atmosphere of reading in community.\n\n7:30 PM – Reading Break \n\nChat with your neighbor! Ask them what they are reading.\nGrab a snack or drink at the bar\nCheck out Feathered Pages' book table\n\n7:40 PM – Break Ends \n\nHead back to the Lapis Theater and do more reading.\n\n8:30 PM – Social Time & Book Chats \n\nShare thoughts on your reads\, favorite passages\, or just connect with fellow book lovers.\n3 raffle winners are announced.\n\n9:00 PM – Event Concludes \n \nThis is our monthly Silent Reading Night\, each month we will have a new theme to inspire your reading. Rediscover the joy of reading in good company at the Hugo House. \nWe can’t wait to read with you!
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-03-19/
CATEGORIES:Community Event
END:VEVENT
